HEDGE RATES AND REDUCED WAREHOUSING COSTS. THE IMPROVEMENT IN MARGINS WAS PARTIALLY OFFSET BY HIGHER SALES INCENTIVES, MOST NOTABLY IN JAPAN, COMBINED WITH EFFORTS TO IMPROVE CONSUMER VALUE IN JAPAN AND KOREA. THE INCREASE IN SELLING AND

ADMINISTRATIVE EXPENSES DURING FISCAL 2007 WAS ATTRIBUTABLE TO INCREASED INVESTMENTS IN DEMAND CREATION, MOST NOTABLY THE JUST DO IT AND FORCE BASKETBALL CAMPAIGNS. OVERALL BUSINESS GROWTH ACROSS THE REGION, COMBINED WITH RETAIL EXPANSION IN CHINA

AND KOREA, ALSO CONTRIBUTED TO AN INCREASE IN OPERATING OVERHEAD EXPENSES.

